posts_info.description: This is their world, we’re just living in it. Jaw-dropping video footage caught the moment a group of hammerhead sharks swarmed boaters and swimmers in the shallow waters of Robinson Island in Alabama over the weekend. Footage posted by Meredith Perry on June 10, shows a school of sharks circling around and between several anchored boats, causing panicked swimmers to scramble out of the water and seek refuge in nearby boats. According to marine biologist, Dr. Kelly Boyle, hammerhead sharks are common in the Gulf of Mexico and are considered harmless to humans as they are more interested in smaller fishes. “It’s good to see them and give them their respect,” she said. #sharks #alabama #florida #ocean #viral #boat #sealife #cheddarnews

It must have been un-bear-ably hot. A young black bear shocked beachgoers by taking a refreshing swim at a crowded beach in Destin, Florida, on Sunday. Footage taken by Chris Barron shows the bear emerging from the cooling turquoise waters before it ran across the beach just inches away from sunbathers and vanished in nearby sand dunes. “The bear was out pretty far. A lot of people started swimming in. I was worried it was a shark. I walked over and thought it was a dog,” Barron said. #florida #beach #bear #wildlife #swimming #beachvibes #viral #cheddarnews

A royal welcome at the Sydney Airport! Photographer Jason Edwards captured the heartwarming moment when John Dixon dressed as a Spartan warrior and greeted his fiancée carrying a sign that read “Queen.” The future bride, Emily Chandler, can be seen bursting into laughter as she approaches, before embracing her spartan husband-to-be as bystanders watched and cheered. #australia #sydney #airport #spartan #surprise #fiancee #viral #cheddarnews

Kilauea, the youngest and most active volcano on the Big Island of Hawaii, erupted early Wednesday morning, sending fountains of lava spewing skyward before pooling and spreading across its summit. The US Geological Survey's Hawaiian Volcano Observatory detected a glow on their camera, and reported that the eruption began around 4:44 am local time. The volcanic eruption carries potential hazards, including volcanic gas and smog which may impact air quality, the USGS warned. #volcano #volcanoeruption #hawaii #bigisland #kilauea #cheddarnews

Mission impawsible! Security footage from inside Minneapolis Animal Care and Control shows a rambunctious pitbull jump over the cement wall at the shelter so she could hang out with her best puppy pal. Brenda and Linda arrived at the shelter late last month as two strays roaming the streets of Minneapolis. One day, staff at the shelter were befuddled to find Brenda hanging out in Linda’s kennel, realizing the inseparable pitties needed to be together. When they watched security footage, staff were awestruck to see Brenda leap over the kennel wall to be with Linda. “Brenda’s jumping abilities are not common!” Danielle Joerger, Minneapolis Animal Care & Control shelter supervisor said. Brenda and Linda have been adopted together and are now with their “furever family,” the shelter wrote in a Facebook post. #dogs #pitbull #BestFriends #shelter #adopt #rescue #minnesota #cheddarnews
